# Changelog

All notable changes to G3 ICAP Server will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.1.0] - 2024-01-XX

### Added
- Initial release of G3 ICAP Server
- Support for ICAP REQMOD, RESPMOD, and OPTIONS methods
- High-performance async server implementation
- YAML-based configuration system
- Content filtering and URL blocking capabilities
- Virus scanning integration support
- TLS/SSL encryption support
- Comprehensive statistics collection
- Prometheus metrics export
- Systemd service integration
- Docker containerization support
- Extensive documentation and examples

### Features
- **Protocol Support**: Full ICAP 1.0 protocol implementation
- **Performance**: Built with Rust for maximum performance and memory safety
- **Security**: TLS support and client IP filtering
- **Monitoring**: Statistics API and Prometheus metrics
- **Configuration**: Flexible YAML configuration with validation
- **Extensibility**: Plugin-based handler system for custom functionality
- **Production Ready**: Systemd integration and proper logging

### Architecture
- Modular design following G3 project patterns
- Async/await based on Tokio runtime
- Comprehensive error handling with custom error types
- Statistics collection with atomic operations
- Service registry for dynamic service management
- Signal handling for graceful shutdown
